defs.name: is_whitespace_char
defs.docs:
Checks whether the given character is a white space character (`S`)
 as is defined by XML 1.1 specification, [section 2.3][1].

defs.name: is_whitespace_str
defs.docs:
Checks whether the given string is compound only by white space
 characters (`S`) using the previous is_whitespace_char to check
 all characters of this string

defs.name: is_name_start_char
defs.docs:
Checks whether the given character is a name start character (`NameStartChar`)
 as is defined by XML 1.1 specification, [section 2.3][1].

defs.name: is_name_char
defs.docs:
Checks whether the given character is a name character (`NameChar`)
 as is defined by XML 1.1 specification, [section 2.3][1].

defs.name: trim_whitespace
defs.docs: Whether or not should whitespace in textual events be removed. Default is false.

defs.name: whitespace_to_characters
defs.docs:
Whether or not should whitespace be converted to characters.
 Default is false.

defs.name: cdata_to_characters
defs.docs:
Whether or not should CDATA be converted to characters.
 Default is false.

defs.name: ignore_comments
defs.docs: Whether or not should comments be omitted. Default is true.

defs.name: coalesce_characters
defs.docs:
Whether or not should sequential `Characters` events be merged.
 Default is true.

defs.name: extra_entities
defs.docs: A map of extra entities recognized by the parser. Default is an empty map.

defs.name: ignore_end_of_stream
defs.docs: Whether or not the parser should ignore the end of stream. Default is false.

defs.name: EmitterConfig
defs.value: EmitterConfig { line_separator, indent_string, perform_indent, perform_escaping, write_document_declaration, normalize_empty_elements, cdata_to_characters, keep_element_names_stack, autopad_comments }
defs.docs: Emitter configuration structure.

defs.name: line_separator
defs.docs: Line separator used to separate lines in formatted output. Default is `"\n"`.

defs.name: indent_string
defs.docs:
A string which will be used for a single level of indentation. Default is `"  "`
 (two spaces).

defs.name: perform_indent
defs.docs: Whether or not the emitted document should be indented. Default is false.

defs.name: perform_escaping
defs.docs: Whether or not characters in output events will be escaped. Default is true.

defs.name: write_document_declaration
defs.docs:
Whether or not to write XML document declaration at the beginning of a document.
 Default is true.

defs.name: normalize_empty_elements
defs.docs: Whether or not to convert elements with empty content to empty elements. Default is true.

defs.name: cdata_to_characters
defs.docs: Whether or not to emit CDATA events as plain characters. Default is false.

defs.name: keep_element_names_stack
defs.docs:
Whether or not to keep element names to support `EndElement` events without explicit names.
 Default is true.

defs.name: autopad_comments
defs.docs:
Whether or not to automatically insert leading and trailing spaces in emitted comments,
 if necessary. Default is true.
